Basic Setup Steps:
1. Write the YAML file
2. cd into the directory where the YAML is
3. Make sure the Docker engine is running
4. docker compose up -d**

**"docker compose up" will basically get the containers set up and ready to run, also allowing them to "talk" to one another. The "-d" option
makes it so your terminal isn't locked to the process after running the command; -d is short for "detached mode".

For more advanced stuff, do more research and record your findings somewhere safe.